<hr>
Due to the coronavirus pandemic, the 2020 league division and championship series and the World Series were played in
neutral parks in Arlington and Houston, Texas and Los Angeles and San Diego, California. The reason was to form "bubbles"
to protect against games being postponed or canceled because of an outbreak of Covid-19. The moves worked well since all
of the games were played as scheduled. <A href="https://www.retrosheet.org/boxesetc/2020/YPS_2020.htm">Click here</A> to
see the 2020 post season games.
<hr>

<pre>
Reasons for move:
(1) Incomplete repairs at Braves Field
(2) Serious structural accident at the Baker Bowl
(3) Threat of Hurricane Ivan in Miami (did not occur)
(4) Alternate home site for Expos
(5) Marketing move by Major League Baseball
(6) Alternate park for Sunday and/or holiday games
(7) Structural accident at Yankee Stadium (falling concrete and steel)
(8) Incomplete football renovations to Oakland-Alameda County Coliseum
(9) Fire at Polo Grounds IV
(10) Collapse of the RF grandstand at Baker Bowl
(11) Opening of the Grand Circuit Trotting Meet in Detroit
(12) To accommodate large crowd
(13) Fire at Huntington Street Grounds
(14) Delay in the opening of Braves Field
(15) Snow and cold weather in Cleveland
(16) Team moved from Chicago and played subsequent home games in Pittsburgh
(17) Hartford played all but one "home" game in Brooklyn
(18) Hurricane Ike in Houston
(19) Hurricane Harvey in Houston
(20) Hurricane Irma in Florida
(21) Canada did not allow Blue Jays to play in Toronto due to coronavirus pandemic
</PRE>
